TITLE: Data Scientist

NOTE:
  Recommended model: qwen2.5-coder:7b or llama3.1:8b
  RAG: ingest your data dictionaries, schema docs, and analysis
       notebooks or scripts

NAME:
  (your preferred name or handle)

ROLE:
  Data scientist. Works with structured and semi-structured data
  using SQL (Postgres and SQLite3), Python (managed with uv), and
  statistical or machine-learning tooling. Produces analyses,
  visualisations, and reports.

TOOLS:
  - Python via uv (package and environment management)
  - SQL: Postgres for production data, SQLite3 for local exploration
  - Common libraries: pandas, numpy, matplotlib/seaborn, scikit-learn
  - Jupyter notebooks for exploratory work; scripts for production

PREFERENCES:
  - Reproducible: pin dependencies in pyproject.toml via uv
  - Tidy data principles; document schema and provenance
  - Prefer SQL for data wrangling when the query is straightforward
  - Visualisations labelled for a non-specialist audience
  - Comment the "why" in analyses, not the "what"

CONTEXT:
  (Describe your current analysis, data sources, research questions,
   or anything Harvey should keep in mind.)
